<Folder><name>Waypoints</name><Placemark><name>Bad Mergentheim</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>9.774000,49.492000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Weikersheim</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>9.898000,49.479000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Rothenburg ob der Tauber</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.178600,49.379500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Feuchtwangen</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.332200,49.165000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Dinkelsbühl</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.318600,49.071000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Nördlingen</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.488000,48.852000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Harburg</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.692000,48.786000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Donauwörth</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.776200,48.718000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Augsburg</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.897800,48.370500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Landsberg am Lech</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.881000,48.048000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Schongau</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.900000,47.809000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Wieskirche (spur)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.900000,47.681000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Schwangau (Neuschwanstein)</name><styleUrl>#wpt</styleUrl><Point><coordinates>10.749700,47.557700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
<Folder><name>Scenic Points</name><Placemark><name>Würzburg Residenz</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[UNESCO Rococo palace (1720–44) of the Würzburg prince-bishops. Tiepolo's ceiling fresco above the staircase is the largest in the world. Würzburg's Franconian Riesling is exceptional.]]></description><Point><coordinates>9.953400,49.791300,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Rothenburg ob der Tauber</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Walled medieval town, fully preserved (then carefully reconstructed after WWII bombing). Walk the wall complete circuit, 90 min. Christmas Museum operates year-round.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.178600,49.379500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Dinkelsbühl</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Less visited than Rothenburg, just as preserved — 700-year-old townscape, rainbow gables, complete city wall. Authoritative consensus: more atmospheric, fewer tour buses.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.318600,49.071000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Nördlingen</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Built inside the Nördlinger Ries — a 25 km-wide meteor crater from 14.6 million years ago. The town's St. Georg church tower contains rocks made from the impact. Climb 350 steps for panorama into the crater rim.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.488000,48.852000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Augsburg / Fuggerei</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Founded by the Roman emperor in 15 BC. The Fuggerei (1521) is the world's oldest still-functioning social housing complex — rent for residents has been 1 Rhine guilder per year (about €0.88) for 500 years.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.897800,48.370500,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Wieskirche</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[UNESCO Rococo pilgrimage church (1745–54) standing alone in a meadow. Inside is one of the masterpieces of European Baroque — intentional theatrical light, painted clouds dissolving into real ones.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.900000,47.681000,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark><Placemark><name>Schloss Neuschwanstein</name><styleUrl>#poi</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Ludwig II's castle, 1869–86, built when castles were already 300 years out of fashion. Inspired Disney's Sleeping Beauty Castle. Reservations essential; tours sold out weeks ahead in summer.]]></description><Point><coordinates>10.749700,47.557700,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark></Folder>
